Quick instructions how to build smash.
SMASH is known to compile and work on gcc >= 4.8 and clang >= 3.2,
as it uses c++11 features. It also needs the GNU Scientific Library.

Build it in a seperate directory:
  mkdir build
  cd build
  cmake ../
  make

Run it with specific settings:
  vi config_general.txt
  ./smash

Run the various tests:
  make test

Tarball mash:
  ./bin/smash_tarball
